, Somerset, England":"英国薩默塞特可瑟爾斯同","Taunton, Somerset, England":"英国薩默塞特陶頓","lifeSummary":"当Geoffrey De Stawell于1270年出生在英国薩默塞特陶頓时，他的父亲Matthew de Stawell51岁，母亲Anastasia Brent51岁。他于1285年与Jane de Colombières在英国薩默塞特可瑟爾斯同结婚。他们至少是1个儿子和2个女儿的父母。他去世于1325年在他的家乡享年55岁，埋葬在英国薩默塞特陶頓。"},"hr":{"1270–1325":"1270.–1325.","–Male":"preminuo","1268–Female":"1268–preminula","1288–Female":"1288–preminula","1320–1361":"1320.–1361","–Female":"preminula","1219–1316":"1219–1316.","1219–Female":"1219–preminula","1285":"1285.","1361":"1361","1270":"1270.","1290":"1290","1316":"1316.","1239":"1239.","1315":"1315","1325":"1325.","1268":"1268","1288":"1288","1320":"1320.","about 1288":"oko 1288.","1219":"1219","1317":"1317","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Cothelstone, Somerset, England":"Cothelstone, Somerset, England","Taunton, Somerset, England":"Taunton, Somerset, England"},"cs":{"1270–1325":"1270–1325","–Male":"Zesnulý","1268–Female":"1268–Zesnulá","1288–Female":"1288–Zesnulá","1320–1361":"1320–1361","–Female":"Zesnulá","1219–1316":"1219–1316","1219–Female":"1219–Zesnulá","1285":"1285","1361":"1361","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1239":"1239","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","1268":"1268","1288":"1288","1320":"1320","about 1288":"okolo 1288","1219":"1219","1317":"1317","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Anglie","Cothelstone, Somerset, England":"Cothelstone, Somerset, Anglie","Taunton, Somerset, England":"Taunton, Somerset, Anglie"},"da":{"1270–1325":"1270–1325","–Male":"Afdød","1268–Female":"1268–Afdød","1288–Female":"1288–Afdød","1320–1361":"1320–1361","–Female":"Afdød","1219–1316":"1219–1316","1219–Female":"1219–Afdød","1285":"1285","1361":"1361","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1239":"1239","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","1268":"1268","1288":"1288","1320":"1320","about 1288":"omkring 1288","1219":"1219","1317":"1317","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Cothelstone, Somerset, England":"Cothelstone, Somerset, England","Taunton, Somerset, England":"Taunton, Somerset, England"},"nl":{"1270–1325":"1270–1325","–Male":"Overleden","1268–Female":"1268–Overleden","1288–Female":"1288–Overleden","1320–1361":"1320–1361","–Female":"Overleden","1219–1316":"1219–1316","1219–Female":"1219–Overleden","1285":"1285","1361":"1361","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1239":"1239","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","1268":"1268","1288":"1288","1320":"1320","about 1288":"circa 1288","1219":"1219","1317":"1317","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Cothelstone, Somerset, England":"Cothelstone, Somerset, England","Taunton, Somerset, England":"Taunton, Somerset, England"},"en":{"1270–1325":"1270–1325","–Male":"Deceased","1268–Female":"1268–Deceased","1288–Female":"1288–Deceased","1320–1361":"1320–1361","–Female":"Deceased","1219–1316":"1219–1316","1219–Female":"1219–Deceased","1285":"1285","1361":"1361","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1239":"1239","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","1268":"1268","1288":"1288","1320":"1320","about 1288":"about 1288","1219":"1219","1317":"1317","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Cothelstone, Somerset, England":"Cothelstone, Somerset, England","Taunton, Somerset, England":"Taunton, Somerset, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"De","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Stawell","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Stowell  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Stowell","meanings":["English: habitational name from Stowell (Somerset), Stowell (Gloucestershire), East and West Stowell in Wilcot (Wiltshire), or Stawell (Somerset), all named with Old English <i>stān</i> ‘stone, rock’ + <i>wella</i> ‘well, spring, stream’. The surname was taken to the Isle of Man by 1511, from whence it migrated to Lancashire and Yorkshire."]}]},{"name":"Geoffrey","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Germanic (Frankish and Lombard) origin, introduced to Britain by the Normans. It was in regular use among the counts of Anjou, ancestors of the English royal house of Plantagenet, who were descended from Geoffrey Plantagenet, Count of Anjou (  1113–51 ). It was a particularly popular name in England and France in the later Middle Ages; notable bearers in England include the poet  Geoffrey Chaucer  (  <i>c.</i>1340–1400 ) and in Wales the chronicler  Geoffrey  of Monmouth (  d. 1155 ). The original form and meaning of the name is disputed. According to one theory, it is merely a variant of   Godfrey ;  others derive the first part from the Germanic word <i>gawia</i> ‘territory’, <i>walah</i> ‘stranger’, or <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’. Medieval forms can be found to support all these theories, and it is possible that several names have fallen together, or that the name was subjected to reanalysis by folk etymology at an early date."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":20,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":45,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Geoffrey De Stawell was born in 1270, in Taunton, Somerset, England, his father, Matthew de Stawell, was 51 and his mother, Anastasia Brent, was 51. He married Jane de Colombières in 1285, in Cothelstone, Somerset, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. He died in 1325, in his hometown, at the age of 55, and was buried in Taunton, Somerset, England."},"et":{"1270–1325":"1270–1325","–Male":"Surnud","1268–Female":"1268–Surnud","1288–Female":"1288–Surnud","1320–1361":"1320–1361","–Female":"Surnud","1219–1316":"1219–1316","1219–Female":"1219–Surnud","1285":"1285","1361":"1361","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1239":"1239","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","1268":"1268","1288":"1288","1320":"1320","about 1288":"umbes 1288","1219":"1219","1317":"1317","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Cothelstone, Somerset, England":"Cothelstone, Somerset, England","Taunton, Somerset, England":"Taunton, Somerset, England"},"fi":{"1270–1325":"1270–1325","–Male":"Kuollut","1268–Female":"1268–Kuollut","1288–Female":"1288–Kuollut","1320–1361":"1320–1361","–Female":"Kuollut","1219–1316":"1219–1316","1219–Female":"1219–Kuollut","1285":"1285","1361":"1361","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1239":"1239","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","1268":"1268","1288":"1288","1320":"1320","about 1288":"noin 1288","1219":"1219","1317":"1317","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Cothelstone, Somerset, England":"Cothelstone, Somerset, England","Taunton, Somerset, England":"Taunton, Somerset, England"},"fr":{"1270–1325":"1270–1325","–Male":"Décédé","1268–Female":"1268–Décédée","1288–Female":"1288–Décédée","1320–1361":"1320–1361","–Female":"Décédée","1219–1316":"1219–1316","1219–Female":"1219–Décédée","1285":"1285","1361":"1361","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","1316":"1316",